250 g Ground Turkey
9 g Moo Shu Spice Blend
1 unit(s) Peanut Butter
¼ cup Vegetarian Oyster Sauce
½ tbsp Soy Sauce
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
56 g Carrot, julienned
56 g Snow Peas
2 unit(s) Honey
¾ cup Jasmine Rice
½ unit(s) Lime
28 g Peanuts, chopped
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, add 1 cups (2 cups) water and 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) salt to a medium pot. Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Wash and dry all produce.
Using a strainer, rinse rice until water runs clear.
To the boiling water, add rice. Cover and reduce heat to medium-low. Cook for 12-15 min, until rice is tender and water is absorbed. Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, juice half the lime (whole lime for 4 servings).
Halve snow peas.
Heat a large non-stick pan over high.
While it heats, in a large bowl, whisk together peanut butter, oyster sauce, honey, soy sauce, 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) lime juice and 1/3 cup (2/3 cup) water.

When pan is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then turkey. Cook for 2-3 min, breaking up turkey into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.** Season with pepper.
Reduce heat to medium-high.
Add Moo Shu Spice Blend and garlic puree. Cook for 30 sec, stirring constantly, until fragrant.

To the pan with turkey, add carrots and snow peas. Cook 3-4 min, stirring often, until veggies are tender.
Remove the pan from heat, then add peanut mixture. Stir to combine.

Fluff rice with a fork.
Divide rice between bowls.
Top with turkey-veggie mixture.
Sprinkle peanuts over top.